records.addlTxt:
The State moves to amend to misdemeanor possess THC, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(e) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge.   Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for one (1) year.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) Complete thirty (30) hours of community service;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
